The French government said it would signa contract with &lt;Walt Disney Co> on Tuesday for theconstruction of Europe's first Disneyland amusement park.    A statement from the office of Prime Minister JacquesChirac said the project, which will cost some 12 billionfrancs, would create up to 30,000 jobs and be built outsideParis.    Funding will be provided by a combination of bank loans,preferential financing by the French state and privateinvestment. France has also agreed to invest two billion francsto extend rail and road links. REUTER&#3;